This README covers generating recipe scripts from the HPCaaS documentation.

To generate scripts-

	1.) Make sure the input file in create_recipes.sh is correct.
	2.) ./create_recipes.sh



At current, this will publish the 4 recipes the docs generate, the two support scripts, 
the three optional SMS scripts, and a separate README for the flavor.

It is hard coded for a single flavor, 3_hpc_as_a_service, but that can be scripted for future
flavors.

The files generated are:

./3_hpc_as_a_service/prepare_chpc_image
./3_hpc_as_a_service/prepare_cloud_init
./3_hpc_as_a_service/deploy_chpc_openstack 
./3_hpc_as_a_service/prepare_chpc_openstack
./3_hpc_as_a_service/README
./3_hpc_as_a_service/set_os_hpc 
./3_hpc_as_a_service/update_cnodes_to_sms
./3_hpc_as_a_service/sms/enable_genders 
./3_hpc_as_a_service/sms/update_mrsh
./3_hpc_as_a_service/sms/update_clustershell


More will be added as necessary.
